grocery app features:

meal planning calendar with recipe selection and extras
household inventory restock (can choose wholesale option if set in preferences)
use up items ingredient search
grocery list
cook


Settings:
customize recipes
customize inventory
preferences (how often you shop, do you use wholesale, what size family do you cook for, do you most value simplicity, low-cost, speed, least waste, or variety, shortcut/substitution mode available, do you have dietary restrictions, and substitution mode- options are default, more strict, or more leniant, and planned or free flow mode, show/hide optional use up items step, with notifications on or off, and revert to default data)

shortcut mode and substitition mode should be available on any page if set to 'available' so the user can change these settings anytime.

local data that will be stored and can be changed, deleted, or added to:

recipes added (default settings saved for reverting)
ingredients added (default settings saved for reverting)
household goods added (defult settings saved for reverting)
user app preferences saved


example structure for recipe data:

// recipe for spaghetti

{	
	id: "spaghetti-bolognese",
	name: "Spaghetti Bolognese",
	cuisine: "Italian",
	dish-type: "main",
	difficulty: "easy",
	price-level: "mid",
	time-requirement: "short",
	multi-tasking: "possible",
	shortcut-replaces: "no",
	ingredients: [
		// ["ingredient-id","quantity","unit","shortcut-substitute"]
		["spaghetti","16","oz""none"],
		["tomato-sauce","8","oz","spaghetti-sauce"],
		["mushrooms","6","oz","omit"],
		["basil","0.5","tsp","omit"],
		["oregano","0.5","tsp","omit"],
		["salt","0.5","tsp","none"],
		["ground-beef","1","lb","none"]
	],
	steps: [
	    // ["step-name","step text","shortcut-replacement"]
	    ["prepare sides","Prepare any desired sides for the meal.","no-shortcut"],
	    ["boil pasta","Fill a pot half to 3/4 full of water and bring to a boil, adding the pasta and allowing to cook while the meat is prepared, stirring occasionally.","no-shortcut"],
		["cook beef","Brown the ground beef on medium heat on the stove in a pan, seasoning it with salt (along with mushrooms, if using).","no-shortcut"],
		["make sauce","Add the tomato sauce, basil, and oregano to the meat, mixing and continuing to cook on medium heat until fragrant and thoroughly heated.","Add the spaghetti sauce to the meat, mix, and heat thoroughly."],
		["drain pasta","Once pasta is cooked to desired consistency, drain and serve the pasta with the meat sauce over it.","no-shortcut"]
	],
	recommended-sides: [
		["yeast-rolls"],
		["ceasar-salad"]
	]

}


